[2] Niger
Date: Fri, 3 Mar 2006
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Outbreak Reports [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2006_03_03/en/index.html>

Meningococcal disease in Niger
------------------------------
The Ministry of Health has reported a total of 614 cases and 44 deaths from
1 Jan to 26 Feb 2006. The epidemic threshold has been crossed in 2
neighboring districts, Madarounfa and Guidan-Roumdji. Over 40 specimens of
cerebrospinal fluid have been found positive for _Neisseria meningitidis_
serogroup A.
Following a request from the Ministry of Health, the International
Coordinating Group (ICG) on Vaccine Provision for Epidemic Meningitis
Control has provided 750 000 doses of bivalent vaccine and 7800 vials of
oily chloramphenicol for case management. An immunization campaign has
started in both districts, with the support from international agencies and
nongovernmental organizations.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[These districts are in Maradi in the south of the country. For a map
see <http://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/africa/ne.htm> - Mod.LL]
